  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Regional Migrant Response Plan (RMRP) for the Horn of Africa and Yemen 2021-2024 to Provide Protection and Assistance for Vulnerable Migrants in Yemen</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The East and Horn of Africa is a region of origin, transit, and destination for hundreds of thousands of migrants, the majority of whom travel in an irregular manner often relying on unscrupulous smugglers to facilitate movement along the Eastern Route via Somalia, and Djibouti with the hope of crossing the Gulf of Aden into Yemen and onwards towards the Gulf states with the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia as the main destination for the majority. The persistent vulnerability of migrants in irregular situations is one of the specific drivers of migration and determinants of IOM&#x2019;s response through the Regional Migrant Response Plan (MRP). This project focuses mainly on providing life-saving assistance to vulnerable migrants and host communities.  Additionally, it will provide quality, timely and inclusive protection assistance and services to migrants and host communities, but is also flexible and includes activities which build evidence, partnerships, and coordination to enhance humanitarian response and migration management throughout the migration route, as prioritized by the countries and the Regional Office in Nairobi.</narrative>
  </description>
